    "title": "Enhanced Vegetation Index 2 (EVI2)",
    "description": "Calculates the Enhanced Vegetation Index 2 (EVI2) from Sentinel-2 L2A imagery. EVI2 is a two-band vegetation index derived from near-infrared (B08) and red (B04) reflectance, designed to strengthen the vegetation signal in dense canopies while reducing sensitivity to soil background and atmospheric influences. Results are rendered using a fixed threshold-to-RGB color ramp for intuitive interpretation from low to high vegetation signal. Adapted from a SentinelHub Custom Script by Authors not listed.",
